                            <comment id="15647684" author="githubbot" created="Tue, 8 Nov 2016 14:20:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;GitHub user tillrohrmann opened a pull request:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/2771&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/2771&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-5033&quot; title=&quot;CEP operators don&amp;#39;t properly advance time&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-5033&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-5033&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;cep&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; Advance time with incoming watermarks at CEP operator&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Before the time was only advanced if the CEP had some events buffered. If the priority queue&lt;br/&gt;
    was empty, then an incoming watermark did not advance the time. This led to missing timeouts&lt;br/&gt;
    and pruning possibilities. The PR fixes this problem.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You can merge this pull request into a Git repository by running:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    $ git pull &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/tillrohrmann/flink&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/tillrohrmann/flink&lt;/a&gt; fixCEPAdvancingTime&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Alternatively you can review and apply these changes as the patch at:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/2771.patch&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/2771.patch&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To close this pull request, make a commit to your master/trunk branch&lt;br/&gt;
with (at least) the following in the commit message:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    This closes #2771&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;commit 4643fb9ffd6c5f8db3525cf96c660f017bde821c&lt;br/&gt;
Author: Till Rohrmann &amp;lt;trohrmann@apache.org&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Date:   2016-11-08T14:14:36Z&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-5033&quot; title=&quot;CEP operators don&amp;#39;t properly advance time&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-5033&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-5033&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;cep&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; Advance time with incoming watermarks at CEP operator&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Before the time was only advanced if the CEP had some events buffered. If the priority queue&lt;br/&gt;
    was empty, then an incoming watermark did not advance the time. This led to missing timeouts&lt;br/&gt;
    and pruning possibilities. The PR fixes this problem.&lt;/p&gt;

